    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="346"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">674.84A/5–1151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_GWS1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gifford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-11T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 11, 1951—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5894. For the Secretary. At reception given by <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Morrison</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_KCDB1">King</persName> and
                    Queen of Denmark last night, in response to question by me as to how things
                    where going with him, he stated with some feeling that Iran was giving him
                    concern and he hoped for US support. I said I was sure he could count on it in
                    any constructive program UK might have. It seemed significant to me that he held
                    up receiving line to tell me this as I shook hands with him.</p>
                <p>Today I had lunch alone with <persName corresp="#p_DA1">Anthony Eden</persName>
                    at his request. He said he had talked with <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Morrison</persName> about Iran with <persName corresp="#p_CWL1"
                        >Churchill</persName> present, <persName corresp="#p_DA1">Eden</persName>
                    told <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Morrison</persName> he felt oil sit in other
                    parts of Near East wld tend to degenerate if Iran won out which it might unless
                    something constructive were done by UK. <persName corresp="#p_DA1"
                        >Eden</persName> suggested to <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Morrison</persName>
                    that UK shld force Suez Canal issue by sending destroyers with tankers thru Suez
                    Canal and insisting on oil being transported freely thru canal. He seemed to
                    believe that UK wld get away with it with Egypt and that it wld convince <gloss
                        target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss> area that UK meant business and wld have salutary
                    effect on Iran. I am not sure that <persName corresp="#p_DA1">Eden</persName>
                    knew all the facts about Suez Canal but what he was saying was that the use of
                    big stick directly in Suez wld be better than directly in Iran which might bring
                    Soviets in from North. I expressed no view on matter but he gave me to
                    understand that he expected me to pass his remarks on to his friend, <persName
                        corresp="#p_ADG1">Dean Acheson</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gifford</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
